# Fix Verification for task-1778215785-c96e

## Problem
gh pr list requires git repository context and fails with "not a git repository" when run from app bundle directory.

## Solution
Replaced `gh pr list` with `gh search prs` which works from any directory.

## Verification Tests

### Test 1: Old command fails outside git repo
```
$ cd /tmp && /opt/homebrew/bin/gh pr list --author @me --json number,title
failed to run git: fatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git
❌ FAIL - Requires git repo context
```

### Test 2: New command works outside git repo
```
$ cd /tmp && /opt/homebrew/bin/gh search prs --author=@me --json number,title --limit 1
[{"number":897126,"title":"Lisatok pyapi 197 python rpc optimasation backup 2"}]
✅ PASS - Works from any directory
```

### Test 3: Build verification
```
$ xcodebuild -project PRDesk.xcodeproj -scheme PRDesk -configuration Debug build
** BUILD SUCCEEDED **
✅ PASS
```

### Test 4: Integration test
```
$ swift test_github_client_integration.swift
✅ PASS: fetchMyPRs succeeded
   Found 30 PRs
   First PR: #897126 - Lisatok pyapi 197 python rpc optimasation backup 2
   Repository: Canva/canva
   State: closed, Draft: false
   Updated: 2026-04-23 15:11:34 +0000
✅ PASS - Correctly parses repository.nameWithOwner
```

## Changes Made

### PullRequest.swift
- Replaced `headRepository: Repository?` and `headRepositoryOwner: RepositoryOwner` with `repository: Repository`
- Updated Repository struct to include `nameWithOwner: String`
- Simplified `repositoryFullName` computed property

### GitHubClient.swift
- Changed command from `gh pr list` to `gh search prs`
- Updated arguments from `["pr", "list", "--author", "@me"]` to `["search", "prs", "--author=@me"]`
- Updated fields from `headRepository,headRepositoryOwner` to `repository`

## Result
All acceptance criteria met:
✅ Successfully fetches and parses PR list
✅ Returns empty array for empty responses
✅ Handles gh CLI not available
✅ Build succeeds
✅ Works from any directory (no git repo required)
